UML:TaggedValue.value: Abstract schema Core Data Types does not depend on other conceptual schemas.

data type whose values are named individually in the model This stereotype does not add additional semantics to UML. It merely enables adding tagged values whose purpose is to improve semantic interoperability in a structured way. The semantic tagged values are defined on and inherited from the abstract stereotype GI_Element. An enumeration and a data type with stereotype GI_CodeSet have in common that their values are specified individually. An enumeration's values are specified individually within the model the enumeration is defined in, whereas the values of a data type with stereotype GI_CodeSet are specified individually beyond the model the data type is defined in.

data type whose instances are the code values from a particular code set that is managed independently of and outside the conceptual schema. The code set is identified using the tagged values of the stereotype. An enumeration and a data type with stereotype GI_CodeSet have in common that their values are specified individually. An enumeration's values are specified individually within the model the enumeration is defined in, whereas the values of a data type with stereotype GI_CodeSet are specified individually beyond the model the data type is defined in.
The value of "codeList" should be a persistent URI identifying the code list.
package that does not have any subpackages Leaf is deprecated.
Data type whose value domain is the value domain of CharacterString except for end of line characters and newline characters.
type consisting of one and only one of several alternative data types Union is deprecated.
model element identifier in the form of a Internationalized Resource Identifier (IRI) This identifier can be used directly in an encoding suitable for the Semantic Web.
representation of a concept by a sign which denotes it in a domain or subject Preferably, designations are expressed in a natural language.
representation of a concept by an expression that describes it and differentiates it from related concepts It is a common practice to have a single definition for a concept.
expression which serves to give information in addition to the definition Unlike a definition, a description includes for instance notes and examples, see ISO 704.
Realization of the CharacterString type from the ISO 19103 core data types.
The stereotypes Union and CodeList and the provisions that apply to them are deprecated.
conceptual schema that is not implementable without further specification
identifier assigned to a version of the abstract schema
A package with stereotype AbstractSchema shall not contain another package with stereotype AbstractSchema.
The code list may be extended freely if no tagged value codeList is present.
Realization of the IRI type from the ISO 19103 core data types.
/* A data type with stereotype GI_CodeSet shall not own any attributes. */ inv: self.base_DataType.ownedAttribute->isEmpty()

The classifiers in a package with stereotype AbstractSchema should have a name that is unique across that package and all its subpackages.
This recommendation does not apply for any classifiers imported from other packages.
enumerated type that can be extended during the lifetime of the model CodeList is deprecated and superseded by GI_CodeSet, which has a different definition.
